This article is a transcript of a press gaggle with Principal Deputy Press Secretary Eric Schultz, who was en route to the White House Frontiers Conference in Pittsburgh. Schultz discussed a range of topics including US military strikes in Yemen, the release of kidnapped girls in Nigeria, the appointment of a new Secretary General of the United Nations, the upcoming US presidential election, and the resignation of the CEO of Wells Fargo. Schultz emphasized the Obama administration's commitment to science, innovation, and diplomacy in addressing global challenges.